        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>How to: Draw a Line</Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

    <Paragraph>This example shows you how to draw lines by using the Line element. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>To draw a line, create a <Run FontWeight="Bold">Line</Run>
 element. Use its X1 and Y1 properties to set its start point; 
and use its X2 and Y2 properties to set its end point. Finally, set its Stroke and StrokeThickness because a line without a stroke is invisible. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Setting the Fill element for a line has no effect, because a line has no interior.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>The following example draws three lines inside a Canvas element. 
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Example
    </Paragraph>

    <Table CellSpacing="5">
      <TableRowGroup>
        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph FontSize="22"><Run>XAML </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

        <TableRow>
          <TableCell>
            <Paragraph xml:space="preserve" TextAlignment="Left" FontSize="8pt" FontFamily="Courier New"><Run>
&lt;Canvas Height="300" Width="300"> 
&lt;!-- Draws a diagonal line from (10,10) to (50,50). --> 
&lt;Line X1="10" Y1="10" X2="50" Y2="50" Stroke="Black" StrokeThickness="4" /> 
&lt;!-- Draws a diagonal line from (10,10) to (50,50) and moves it 100 pixels to the right. --> 
&lt;Line X1="10" Y1="10" X2="50" Y2="50" StrokeThickness="4" Canvas.Left="100"> 
&lt;Line.Stroke> 
&lt;RadialGradientBrush GradientOrigin="0.5,0.5" Center="0.5,0.5" RadiusX="0.5" RadiusY="0.5"> 
&lt;RadialGradientBrush.GradientStops> 
&lt;GradientStop Color="Red" Offset="0" /> 
&lt;GradientStop Color="Blue" Offset="0.25" /> 
&lt;/RadialGradientBrush.GradientStops> 
&lt;/RadialGradientBrush> 
&lt;/Line.Stroke> 
&lt;/Line> 
&lt;!-- Draws a horizontal line from (10,60) to (150,60). --> 
&lt;Line X1="10" Y1="60" X2="150" Y2="60" Stroke="Black" StrokeThickness="4"/> 
&lt;/Canvas> </Run>

            </Paragraph>

          </TableCell>

        </TableRow>

      </TableRowGroup>

    </Table>

